    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonOrganizationAssociation.java
        ArkCase's PersonOrganizationAssociation JPA entity (mapped to
        acm_person_org_assoc) declares fields including person
        (@ManyToOne to Person, nullable=false; we retype to a sys_user
        reference but mark it conditional because in the polymorphic
        target schema person is required only when party_type=Person -
        so this row's <person/> is correctly empty), organization
        (@ManyToOne to Organization, nullable=false; we retype to a
        core_company reference and mark it conditional - required
        when party_type=Organization, which is THIS row's case),
        personToOrganizationAssociationType (a String column for the
        person-to-organization role - the source for our <role_label>;
        ArkCase models it as a free-form String column with no
        constraints; we preserve the same flexibility via String(100)
        but document Requester / Respondent / Witness as the canonical
        example values), organizationToPersonAssociationType (the
        inverse role - intentionally OMITTED from our target schema
        per AAP Section 0.5.7 since the polymorphic single-direction
        association is sufficient for the POC), description (an
        optional ArkCase free-text annotation slot - intentionally
        OMITTED per AAP Section 0.5.7), primaryContact and
        defaultOrganization (BooleanToString boolean flags -
        intentionally OMITTED per AAP Section 0.5.7 since the POC
        does not require contact-primacy semantics). ArkCase's
        single-table inheritance discriminator (cm_class_name) is
        collapsed in our target by the explicit party_type Choice
        field, which is the AAP-prescribed simplification of ArkCase's
        separate-table approach (acm_person_assoc + acm_person_org_assoc)
        into a single polymorphic table (x_casemgmt_case_party).
        PersonAssociation.java is the primary semantic source for the
        Person branch; PersonOrganizationAssociation.java (THIS file's
        listed source) is the primary semantic source for the
        Organization branch - its person + organization combined
        fields motivated our conditional person/organization invariant.

